<div class=3D"mf-section-0" id=3D"mf-section-0">
<p>Degrees and radians are two units for measuring angles. A circle contain=
s 360 degrees, which is the equivalent of 2=CF=80 radians, so 360=C2=B0 <i>=
and</i> 2=CF=80 radians represent the numerical values for going "once arou=
nd" a circle.<sup id=3D"_ref-1" class=3D"reference" aria-label=3D"Link to R=
eference 1"><a href=3D"https://www.wikihow.com/Convert-Degrees-to-Radians#_=
note-1">[1]</a>
</sup> Sound confusing? Don't worry, you can easily convert degrees to radi=
ans, or from <a href=3D"https://www.wikihow.com/Convert-Radians-to-Degrees"=
 title=3D"Convert Radians to Degrees">radians to degrees</a>, in just a few=
 easy steps.
</p>
